===Etymology===
From Arabic {{ARchar|[[حماس]]}} (ḥamās), an acronym (meaning literally ‘enthusiasm’) for {{ARchar|حركة المقاومة الاسلامية}} (ḥarakat al-muqāwama al-islāmīya) ‘Islamic Resistance Movement’.

===Proper noun===
'''Hamas'''

# An [[Islamic]] [[fundamentalist]] organisation that presses for an [[independent]] [[Palestinian]] [[theocracy]] and opposes [[peace]] with [[Israel]].

